Experience at Pru really depends on the team you join.
1. Some departments are just full of gossips and drama;
2. Management may not support internal transfer so there has been a lot of employees leaving the company; what's odd, some managers have information from HR to see employees application and connect to hiring managers before candidate's interview;
3. Some teams spend too much time on infight and thinking instead of working;
4. Some leaders are young and the employees have to take the negative impact of immature leadership style;
5. Some teams are top heavy. Hard to get a piece of work to show ability to next level, and hence no opportunity for advancement. The directors and VPs take most of the budget of the team and they have to do lower level's job to keep their current jobs.
6. Some managers do not understand the meaning of career discussion, so employees leave without even seeing opportunities inside.
7. Racism/favorism.
Advice to Management
Do not micromanage; allow employee to communicate; reduce key man risk by promoting knowledge sharing;
Helpful (1)
